


# Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Elo/Glicko Ranking System

**Project Type:** Collaborative Group Project (3 Members)
**Tools:** Microsoft Excel, Google Sheets, Mathematical Modeling

###  Project Overview

This project is a comprehensive data collection and ranking system designed to track competitive *Super Smash Bros. Ultimate* performance within a local gaming club.

Developing this system was a **shared effort among three equal contributors**. Over the course of two years, our team collectively managed the data lifecycleâ€”from manual data entry of raw match logs to the implementation of complex statistical formulas for the leaderboard.

###  The Team & Contributions

This project was built through the equal collaboration of 3 team members. Workload was distributed evenly across the following areas:

* 
**Data Engineering:** Co-managed a relational database of **500+ match records**, ensuring consistent logging of stages, stocks, and character matchups.


* **Algorithm Implementation:** Collaboratively researched and implemented Elo and Glicko rating formulas in a spreadsheet environment without external plugins.
* **Quality Assurance:** Shared responsibility for "data hygiene," regularly auditing logs to identify and correct data entry errors to maintain leaderboard integrity.

**Contributors:**

